<ul>
<li id="firefox-keywords">
<p>
<b>Assigning Konqueror-like Firefox Shortcuts</b> - these are called keywords
in Firefox terminology. Start firefox, go to a page with a search box
(say <a href="http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/Main_Page">the Vim wikia</a>),
press the right-mouse button, and select “Add a Keyword for this Search”. Then
select a name for the bookmark, and a keyword (say “vim” for our example) and
where to put it. Then you can type “vim unicode” at the address bar
(accessible using Alt+D) to search using this keyword.
</p>
<p>
See <a href="http://www.mozilla.org/products/firefox/smart-keywords.html">this
page in www.mozilla.org about “smart keywords”</a> for more information.
</p>
</li>
</ul>
